text:
does anyone know/is it even possible to alter the `contents` of a blog listing template to have the objects ordered by "most popular" instead of the default "most recent"?
reason: Client wants a dropdown to switch the returned list of blog posts between most recent/most popular, something like:
```
{% if request.query_dict.sortby == 'popular' %}
  {# contents should have posts ordered by popularity #}
  {% for content in contents %}
  ... blog post markup ...
  {% endfor %}
{% else %}
  {# default contents list of posts #}
  {% for content in contents %}
  ... blog post markup ...
  {% endfor %}
{% endif %}
```
Using some javascript, I know I can append a query-string parameter to the URL when the dropdown option is selected, and have it persist through pagination, but...
my assumption, there isn't a way to override the default `contents` list of objects, and the HubSpot `{% post_listing %}` module doesn't appear to work with pagination

So would it be something like this <@U38EZFVFE>

```
&lt;div class="blog-filters"&gt;
            &lt;button data-filter="*" class="active"&gt;All&lt;/button&gt;
            {% set tags = blog_tags("default") %}
            {% for tag in tags %}
              &lt;button data-filter=".{{ tag.slug }}"&gt;{{ tag.name }}&lt;/button&gt;
            {% endfor %}
          &lt;/div&gt;

          &lt;section class="posts-grid"&gt;
            &lt;div id="most-popular"&gt;
              {% set pop_posts = blog_popular_posts('default', 9) %}
              {% for pop_post in pop_posts %}
               &lt;article class="post all" data-category="{% for topic in rec_post.topic_list %}{{ topic.slug }} {% endfor %}"&gt;
                  &lt;div class="post-title"&gt;{{ pop_post.name }}&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;/article&gt;
              {% endfor %}
            &lt;/div&gt;
```

I've tried to overwrite it

```
$(function(){
  var mostPopular = $('.blog-filters button').filter("[data-filter='all']");
  var postsGrid = $('.posts-grid article');

   if (mostPopular).hasClass('active') {
     $(postsGrid).filter("[data-category='all']").css('display','block');
   };
});```
